        <num>36-80-2</num>
        <content>
          <p>Counties, municipalities, county boards of education, and other political subdivisions of the state which are authorized to levy taxes shall have the power and authority, within the limitations prescribed by Article IX, Section V, Paragraph V of the Constitution of Georgia, to issue notes, certificates, or other evidence of indebtedness in anticipation of the collection of taxes levied or to be levied during the calendar year.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1963, p. 450, ยง 1; Ga. L. 1983, p. 3, ยง 57.)</p>
